						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">teaguecl wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">- compatibility with modern TV's and displays.   HDMI anyone?</div><br />HDMI is complicated and probably involves a whole bunch of patent licensing.</div> Fortunately it's just DVI. The only complications come from HDCP, which as a transmitter you can ignore.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><em>stuff about NTSC compatibility</em></div> Oh, augh, please no. Just upscale it to 480p and stop there -- when I look at 240p content displayed as 480i even with a good interlacer it looks awful. A lot of things in NES games have been designed to be exactly one pixel high, and if it jitters vertically as a 480i signal implies it looks terrible.</div>

